# Review Mode

Use Review Mode to inspect work without modifying code.

Read and follow:

- `docs/agents/modes/review.md`
- active ExecPlan
- active repo task
- changed files
- validation output
- `ARCHITECTURE.md`
- relevant source-of-truth docs

Review must verify:

- task scope was respected
- Forbidden Scope was not touched
- Technology Context is defined
- `.harness/stack.env` matches Technology Context
- validation commands passed
- Business Behavior matches accepted docs
- no invented behavior was added
- no risky side effects were introduced
- OPEN_DECISIONs were not bypassed

Review may edit `docs/QUALITY_SCORE.md` only. Review must not fix code or other docs unless explicitly asked.

Before `APPROVED_FOR_HUMAN_REVIEW` or `APPROVED_FOR_CODEX_AUDIT`, update `docs/QUALITY_SCORE.md` with evidence-based, conservative scores. Block approval if review evidence is incomplete.

Report:

- approved / changes requested / blocked
- evidence
- changed files reviewed
- checks reviewed
- QUALITY_SCORE update (what changed; or why blocked)
- risks
- OPEN_DECISIONs
- whether Codex Audit is required
